From 311b0354a44c7d6e2fb294e6f4f3867cb3842e94 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Enrique Parodi Spalazzi <enrique.parodi@airbus.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 23:55:39 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat[cli]: audit, renames, and shell completion
 infrastructure

Normalize help text across every cli_* binary to imperative form
("Run a sen kernel", not "runs a sen kernel"), tighten descriptions,
fix a bracket mismatch in cli_remote_shell's positional hint, and
remove dead code (getEnumerators and the local toSnakeCase /
isUpperCamelCase duplicated across packages).

Rename subcommands and options to match the docker/gh/terraform
conventions while keeping the old names as hidden aliases so existing
scripts and CMake call-sites keep working: `sen gen` to `sen generate`,
`sen fileToArray` to `sen file-to-array`, `sen gen exp_package` to
`sen generate cpp exports`, and `--base_path` to `--base-path`.
Aliases are marked `->group("")`, which hides them from --help and
flags them deprecated in the spec so completion scripts omit them.

Add a cli_common library that exposes a JSON spec format for CLI
apps (via buildSpecJson and a `--dump-spec` runtime hook) and the
addChoice helper that surfaces IsMember choice lists into the spec,
with an overload that carries per-choice descriptions. Every cli_*
binary now calls dumpSpecIfRequested before CLI11_PARSE.

Add a shell-completion pipeline under apps/cli_gen/src/completions:
cli_gen runs each binary with --dump-spec, merges the specs, and
renders self-contained bash, zsh, fish and PowerShell scripts. The
scripts do not call sen at runtime so completion stays fast. Shells
that support descriptions (zsh, fish, PowerShell) render them next
to each candidate; bash falls back to plain names. Already-typed
non-value flags are filtered out of further suggestions, and --help
and --version are surfaced to match docker/gh/terraform. The internal
--dump-spec flag, the one-shot `sen completion` subcommand, and the
internal `sen generate completions` subcommand are hidden from both
--help and the generated completion scripts.

Consolidate the scattered case-conversion helpers into a new
libs/core/base/string_case module (plus unit tests), and update
cli_package and lang/fom_document_set to use it. The module adds
toPascalCase alongside the flattening toUpperCamelCase, with a
doc-comment footgun note on the difference between the two.

Docs: rename every `sen gen` snippet to `sen generate`, fix the
pre-existing MKDocs section title typos, add root-level snippets
for `sen generate uml` and `sen generate mkdocs` (for symmetry with
cpp), add a `C++ exports` subsection, and add a new "Shell completion"
section covering bash, zsh, fish and PowerShell setup.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
