+
+## Shell completion
+
+Sen can emit completion scripts for `bash`, `zsh`, `fish`, and PowerShell. The
+scripts are self-contained: once installed they do not invoke `sen` at
+runtime, so completion stays fast even on cold shells.
+
+```title="sen completion"
+--8<-- "snippets/sen_completion.sh"
+```
+
+### bash
+
+`bash` completion requires **bash 4 or newer** (associative arrays). This is
+the default on most modern distributions; older systems will need an upgrade.
+
+```bash
+# system-wide (requires the bash-completion package)
+sen completion bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/sen
+
+# or for the current user only
+sen completion bash > ~/.local/share/bash-completion/completions/sen
+```
+
+### zsh
+
+```zsh
+# ensure a user-owned completions directory is on your $fpath
+mkdir -p "${HOME}/.zsh/completions"
+sen completion zsh > "${HOME}/.zsh/completions/_sen"
+
+# then in ~/.zshrc
+fpath=(~/.zsh/completions $fpath)
+autoload -Uz compinit && compinit
+```
+
+### fish
+
+```fish
+sen completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/sen.fish
+```
+
+Fish picks up the new completions on its next shell start; run
+`fish_update_completions` or start a fresh shell to see them immediately.
+
+### PowerShell
+
+```powershell
+sen completion powershell | Out-String | Invoke-Expression
+
+# to make it persistent, append it to your profile
+sen completion powershell >> $PROFILE
 ```
